The evidence with the title 'Wage stagnation in nine charts | Economic Policy Institute ' says Jan 6, 2015  ... Congress and the president can pursue the return to full employment by making public investments that can create both jobs and future productivity growth  ... . From 1973 to 2013 , hourly compensation of a typical (production/nonsupervisory) Worker rose just 9 percent while productivity increased 74 percent . 
